<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Envelope_arm  Type: envelope_approval_select 
   <express_ref linkend="envelope:arm:Envelope_arm.envelope_approval_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Envelope_arm.envelope_approval_select">
This extends an approval_item to allow the envelope to be approved. The approval is to be interpreted as approving that the message contained in the envelope is approved to be sent to the identified recipients. There is an implied constraint on the process that recipients cannot be added or removed after the approval is given.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Envelope_arm  Type: envelope_date_time_select 
   <express_ref linkend="envelope:arm:Envelope_arm.envelope_date_time_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Envelope_arm.envelope_date_time_select">
This extends date_or_date_time_item to allow dates and times to be associated with an envelope. An envelope may have associated with it a date sent, for which Date_or_date_time_assigment.role is given the value "Envelope sent".
In the receiving system, an envelope may also have a reception date, for which Date_or_date_time_assigment.role is given the value "Envelope received".
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Envelope_arm  Type: envelope_person_organisation_select 
   <express_ref linkend="envelope:arm:Envelope_arm.envelope_person_organisation_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Envelope_arm.envelope_person_organisation_select">
This extends organization_or_person_in_organization_item to allow one or more recipients to be associated with the envelope. The rganization_or_person_in_organization_assignment.role is given the value "Envelope recipient".
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Envelope_arm  Type: envelope_property_select 
   <express_ref linkend="envelope:arm:Envelope_arm.envelope_property_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Envelope_arm.envelope_property_select">
This extends property_assignment_select to allow properties to be assigned to an envelope. There are no properties predefined in this module.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Envelope_arm  Entity: Envelope  
   <express_ref linkend="envelope:arm:Envelope_arm.Envelope"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Envelope_arm.Envelope">
An Envelope provides an historical record of its transmission. It is used to record the audit data for sending and acknowleding the transmission of a Message.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Envelope_arm  Entity: Envelope  Attribute: acknowledge 
   <express_ref linkend="envelope:arm:Envelope_arm.Envelope.acknowledge"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Envelope_arm.Envelope.acknowledge">
The acknowledge attribute is used to ask for and provide acknowledgement of receipt of the envelope. On transmission of a message, acknowledge may take the values "" (blank), "ask message arrival" or "ask message read".
A blank value expects no reply. A value of "ask message arrival" asks if the message arrived at the recepients mailbox, and requires the reply envelope to have values "acknowledge arrival" if the message arrives at the destination organization_or_person_in_organization, or "delivery failure" if failure of the delivery is detected.
<note> Envelope is used to provide an audit trail. There is no assumption that the transmission system has any knowledge of Envelope or its usage. However, if it reports some failure, that can then be recorded in the way described. </note>
A value of "ask message read" asks if the recipient has actually opened the message to read it, and expects the reply "acknowledge read" on success, or "contents corrupt" if it is not possible to for it to be read.
<note> For any single envelope, there should be an acknowledgement per recipient. The acknowledgement will not contain a message.</note> 
</ext_description>
